"title": "2585: Jesus Christ, trial of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2585: jesus christ, trial of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Jesus Christ, falsely accused of blasphemy towards God and treason towards Rome, humbly endured his trial as a fulfilment of the purposes of God.</p>\n<h2>The preliminary hearing before Annas</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:12-John18:14\">JHN 18:12–18:14</a> <em>Annas, though deposed from office by the Romans, was probably still regarded by many as the true high priest</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:19-John18:23\">JHN 18:19–18:23</a></p>\n<h2>The trial before Caiaphas and the Sanhedrin</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is sent to the ruling high priest</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:57\">MAT 26:57</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:53\">MRK 14:53</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:24\">JHN 18:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:54\">LUK 22:54</a></p>\n<h3>False evidence is sought</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:59-Matt26:60\">MAT 26:59–26:60</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:55-Mark14:56\">MRK 14:55–14:56</a> <em>The Sanhedrin was the high court of the Jews and consisted of 71 chief priests, elders and teachers of the law, including the high priest who presided.</em></p>\n<h3>False accusations are made</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:60-Matt26:61\">MAT 26:60–26:61</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:57-Mark14:59\">MRK 14:57–14:59</a> <em>A person could only be convicted on the evidence of two or more witnesses.</em></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's trial centres upon his Messianic claims</h2>\n<h3>Jesus declares himself to be the Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:63-Matt26:64\">MAT 26:63–26:64</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:61-Mark14:62\">MRK 14:61–14:62</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:66-Luke22:70\">LUK 22:66–22:70</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is charged with blasphemy</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:65-Matt26:66\">MAT 26:65–26:66</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:63-Mark14:64\">MRK 14:63–14:64</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:1\">MAT 27:1</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:1\">MRK 15:1</a> <em>The Sanhedrin decided that Jesus Christ deserved death but charged him with treason rather than blasphemy.</em></p>\n<h3>Jesus is mocked as the Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:67-Matt26:68\">MAT 26:67–26:68</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:65\">MRK 14:65</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:63-Luke22:65\">LUK 22:63–22:65</a></p>\n<h2>The trial before Pilate</h2>\n<h3>The Sanhedrin hand Jesus Christ over to Pilate</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:2\">MAT 27:2</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:1\">MRK 15:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:1\">LUK 23:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:28-John18:32\">JHN 18:28–18:32</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ accepts the title of king</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:36-John18:37\">JHN 18:36–18:37</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:11\">MAT 27:11</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:2\">MRK 15:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:2-Luke23:3\">LUK 23:2–23:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:9-John19:12\">JHN 19:9–19:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:13\">1TI 6:13</a></p>\n<h3>Pilate decides Jesus Christ is innocent</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:4\">LUK 23:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:14-Luke23:15\">LUK 23:14–23:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:22\">LUK 23:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:38\">JHN 18:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:4-John19:6\">JHN 19:4–19:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:28\">ACT 13:28</a></p>\n<h3>Pilate sends Jesus Christ to Herod</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:5-Luke23:10\">LUK 23:5–23:10</a></p>\n<h3>Herod sends Jesus Christ back to Pilate</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:11-Luke23:12\">LUK 23:11–23:12</a></p>\n<h3>Pilate seeks to release Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:12\">JHN 19:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:15-Matt27:18\">MAT 27:15–27:18</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:6-Mark15:10\">MRK 15:6–15:10</a> <em>Pilate appeals to the crowd on the basis of Jesus Christ's kingship</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:19\">MAT 27:19</a> <em>Pilate is warned by his wife not to get involved</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:16\">LUK 23:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:20\">LUK 23:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:22\">LUK 23:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:38-John18:39\">JHN 18:38–18:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:6\">JHN 19:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:15\">JHN 19:15</a></p>\n<h3>The crowd demand the release of Barabbas and the crucifixion of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:20\">MAT 27:20</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:11\">MRK 15:11</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:21-Matt27:23\">MAT 27:21–27:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:12-Mark15:14\">MRK 15:12–15:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:18\">LUK 23:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:21\">LUK 23:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:23\">LUK 23:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:40\">JHN 18:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:6-John19:7\">JHN 19:6–19:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:12\">JHN 19:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:15\">JHN 19:15</a></p>\n<h3>The crowd's demands prevail</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:15\">MRK 15:15</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:26\">MAT 27:26</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:24\">MAT 27:24</a> <em>Pilate denies responsibility</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:25\">MAT 27:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:23-Luke23:25\">LUK 23:23–23:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:16\">JHN 19:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:13-Acts3:14\">ACT 3:13–3:14</a> <em>The emphasis is on the people's responsibility.</em></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is mocked as king</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:2-John19:3\">JHN 19:2–19:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:27-Matt27:31\">MAT 27:27–27:31</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:16-Mark15:20\">MRK 15:16–15:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:15\">JHN 19:15</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's response to his trial</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:7\">ISA 53:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:62-Matt26:63\">MAT 26:62–26:63</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:60-Mark14:61\">MRK 14:60–14:61</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:12\">MAT 27:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:14\">MAT 27:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:5\">MRK 15:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:9\">LUK 23:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:9\">JHN 19:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:32-Acts8:35\">ACT 8:32–8:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:23\">1PE 2:23</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's trial confirms he is God's servant</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:27-Acts4:28\">ACT 4:27–4:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:10\">ISA 53:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:8-John19:11\">JHN 19:8–19:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:23\">ACT 2:23</a> <em>The outcome of the trial fulfilled God's declared purpose.</em></p>",
